Commentary: David Warner and Australia are underway! Starts from over the wicket and delivers it a bit too straight, on a length, on the pads, David Warner nudges it gently past short leg and calls Usman Khawaja through for a single.
Default_Commentary: 0.1: Shaheen Afridi to David Warner, 1 run.

Commentary: Much better from Shaheen Afridi! On a good length, around off, Usman Khawaja hangs on the back foot and rides on top of the bounce to help it wide of backward square leg. Opens his account with a single.
Default_Commentary: 0.2: Shaheen Afridi to Usman Khawaja, 1 run.

Commentary: Sloppy from the skipper! Shaheen Afridi pitches it up, on off, David Warner covers the line of the ball and pushes it towards wide mid off where Shan Masood is a bit casual as he attempts the stop and lets the ball go through his hands, allowing a run.
Default_Commentary: 0.3: Shaheen Afridi to David Warner, 1 run.

Commentary: FOUR! Edgy but Usman Khawaja has his first boundary! Lands it on a hard length, on off, Usman Khawaja looks to defend it with soft hands off the back foot. Gets an outside edge that goes through the gap between third slip and gully for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 0.4: Shaheen Afridi to Usman Khawaja, Four!

Commentary: FOUR! Usman Khawaja ekes out an outside edge again but it eludes third slip! Shaheen Afridi pulls his length back a touch and bowls it on off, a bit of extra bounce on this one, Usman Khawaja hangs on the back foot as he looks to get on top of the bounce. He gets an outside edge that beats the outstretched left hand of the third slip fielder and races into the third man fence. Afridi gestures to his captain about the positioning of the third slip fielder and wants him a bit close.
Default_Commentary: 0.5: Shaheen Afridi to Usman Khawaja, Four!

Commentary: Fuller in length but angling on the pads, Usman Khawaja brings his wrists into play and clips it neatly in front of square on the leg side. The ball does not have enough legs and the batters collect three.
Default_Commentary: 0.6: Shaheen Afridi to Usman Khawaja, 3 runs.

Commentary: Starts off on a hard length, on middle, Usman Khawaja is a bit hurried but adjusts well to jam this one down into the wickiet.
Default_Commentary: 1.1: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Strays a bit down leg, on a good length, Usman Khawaja gets inside the line and lets it go through.
Default_Commentary: 1.2: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Well bowled! In the channel on off, on a good length, a bit of inward movement, Usman Khawaja watches it closely and leaves the ball alone.
Default_Commentary: 1.3: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Angles it across the left-hander, on a length, outside off, left alone again by Usman Khawaja.
Default_Commentary: 1.4: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Much fuller this time and in the corridor of uncertainty, shaping into the batter, Usman Khawaja lifts his bat and leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Default_Commentary: 1.5: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Delivers it on a hard length, on middle, Usman Khawaja hops from the crease but fails to get on top of the bounce and wears it on the body. A good first over from the debutant.
Default_Commentary: 1.6: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Angling into the batter, on a good length, David Warner lets the ball come to him and tucks it with soft hands in front of short leg.

Default_Commentary: 2.3: Shaheen Afridi to David Warner, Four!

Commentary: At 134.4 clicks, on a full length, outside off, a tempter for Usman Khawaja to drive it through the off side but he decides to leave it alone.

Interest shown by Khurram Shahzad again but the ball looked to be pitched outside leg.

Commentary: Around off, on a length, Usman Khawaja defends it from right under his eyes towards cover. Back-to-back maidens from the debutant.
Default_Commentary: 3.6: Khurram Shahzad to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off, angling across, David Warner is happy to leave the ball alone.
Default_Commentary: 4.1: Shaheen Afridi to David Warner, No run.

Commentary: Swinging into the batter, on a fuller length, outside off, David Warner drives it firmly towards mid off where there is a slight fumble by Shan Masood but the batters opt not to chance his arm.
Default_Commentary: 4.2: Shaheen Afridi to David Warner, No run.

Commentary: At the stumps, on a length, David Warner gets right behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler.

Commentary: Drags his length back and bowls it on off, David Warner uses his feet and stabs the ball onto the deck.

Commentary: Fine effort from the skipper! Khurram Shahzad overpitches slightly as he bowls this one outside off, shaping in as well, David Warner accounts for the inward movement and drives it crisply to the left of Shan Masood at mid off. Masood gives it a chase and does extremely well to slide and saves a run for his side. First runs conceded off the bat by Khurram Shahzad.

Commentary: Swinging in again, outside off, fuller in length, Usman Khawaja covers the line of the ball and pushes it out to cover.

Commentary: Beaten! Back of a length, going away, outside off, David Warner has a flirt at the delivery away from the body and is lucky not to edge this one behind.

Commentary: FOUR! CLASSICAL! Fuller-length delivery around off, David Warner drills this one through the cover region for a boundary.

Commentary: Fuller-length delivery on middle and leg, David Warner flicks the ball to the mid-wicket fielder.

Commentary: Short ball, David Warner ducks under the ball, he looks at the square leg Umpire for a wide but nothing says the Umpire.

Commentary: Gets this one to angle back into the left-hander, on a length, on middle, Usman Khawaja gets forward and clips it towards mid-wicket.

Commentary: Length ball around off, Usman Khawaja shuffles a bit and blocks it to the off-side.
Default_Commentary: 11.6: Aamer Jamal to Usman Khawaja, No run.

Commentary: Starts from over the wicket and bowls it on a yorker length, on middle, David Warner squeezes it out towards point. He wants a single but Usman Khawaja says no and sends him back.

Adding to the woes, the ball raced away to the boundary. Poor from Pakistan to say the least.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! An inspired bowling change by Shan Masood as the debutant Aamer Jamal makes an instant impact in his new spell! Travis Head cannot quite believe his luck! Aamer Jamal charges in from over the wicket and bowls it on a back of a length, angling across the left-hander, outside off, Travis Head hangs back and bends his back to flat it away on the off side. Ends up getting a thickish outside edge due to a bit of extra bounce and it goes straight down the throat of Agha Salman towards the third man region. A big blow for Pakistan late in the day! Mitchell Starc charges in from over the wicket and bowls it on a good length, in the channel on off, there is no need for Shan Masood to play at this but he still goes for the drive away from the body. Gets a feather on it and Alex Carey behind the wickets does the rest. Massive appeal for caught behind but turned down. There was certainly a noise as the ball went past the bat and Pat Cummins takes the review. Australia think they have got their man here. There is a healthy deflection on the front on replays and the UltraEdge confirms it.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Travis Head gets the last wicket and Nathan Lyon will have to wait until the second innings for his 500th Test wicket! Travis Head gives the ball air, on middle, and entices the batter to go for the big heave across the line. Shaheen Afridi accepts the invitation as he swings hard but the ball spins away a touch and he gets a top edge. Commentary: OUT! LBW! NUMBER 500 FOR LYON! He creates history and this is a fantastic review from the Aussies. This is tossed up, full and on middle, goes with the arm, Faheem Ashraf lunges to block but plays down the wrong line and gets hit on the pads. This looks really close and there is a huge shout for it, but the umpire remains unmoved. Pat Cummins has a chat with Lyon and takes the review just in time. Snicko shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates three reds. Lyon has been a long and consistent servant for the Aussies and he thoroughly deserves this moment.
